  "hypothesis": "The dual-momentum concept (absolute + relative momentum) showed genuine OOS alpha in iteration 3 (OOS > IS Sharpe, 7/7 WF windows). The failure was insufficient trade count (23.5 IS) and weak Sharpe (~0.28). This iteration addresses both by: (1) switching to DAILY rebalancing to dramatically increase trade frequency, (2) adding a SHORT leg \u2014 selling the bottom-ranked ETF(s) below their SMA \u2014 to double return generation and create a long/short structure that is more market-neutral, (3) using a shorter 10-day momentum lookback for a faster, more responsive signal. The long/short structure removes beta drag and generates returns in both bull and bear regimes, boosting Sharpe. With 8 ETFs, daily rebalancing, and both long and short legs, we should generate 100+ trades. The core insight: relative momentum across liquid ETFs is a genuine cross-sectional signal. We just need to extract more return from it via short exposure and higher frequency.",
